**Version Used**: 
Visual Studio 2026 v18.0.0

**Steps to Reproduce**:

Create a class library containing an extension method using the new C# 14 extension block syntax:

```
public static class MailMessageExtensions
{
    /// <param name="message">
    /// The <see cref="MailMessage"/> to send.
    /// </param>
    /// <exception cref="ArgumentNullException">
    /// <para><paramref name="message"/> is <see langword="null"/>.</para>
    /// </exception>
    extension(MailMessage message)
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// Sends the message using the default SMTP settings.
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="smtpClientFactory">
        /// The <see cref="ISmtpClientFactory"/>.
        /// </param>
        /// <exception cref="ArgumentNullException">
        /// <para><paramref name="smtpClientFactory"/> is <see langword="null"/>.</para>
        /// </exception>
        public void Send(ISmtpClientFactory smtpClientFactory) 
            => throw new NotImplementedException();
    }
}
```

Enable XML documentation for the project:

```
<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">
    <PropertyGroup>
        ...
        <GenerateDocumentationFile>True</GenerateDocumentationFile>
    </PropertyGroup>
    ...
</Project>
```

Build the project and examine the generated XML documentation.

**Expected Behavior**:

The generated documentation for the method should either merge the documentation from the `extension` block, or have an `<inheritdoc>` pointing to it.

**Actual Behavior**:

The generated documentation for the method has no reference to the documenation from the `extension` block:

```
<member name="M:NBS.Core.Net.Mail.MailMessageExtensions.Send(System.Net.Mail.MailMessage,NBS.Core.Net.Mail.ISmtpClientFactory)">
    <inheritdoc cref="M:NBS.Core.Net.Mail.MailMessageExtensions.&lt;G&gt;$BD2D78579B3497A706F11AA8C4CDB9C3.Send(NBS.Core.Net.Mail.ISmtpClientFactory)"/>
</member>
<member name="T:NBS.Core.Net.Mail.MailMessageExtensions.&lt;G&gt;$BD2D78579B3497A706F11AA8C4CDB9C3.&lt;M&gt;$2F6920F09B8CB52AF42667C967999B1B">
    <param name="message">
    The <see cref="T:System.Net.Mail.MailMessage"/> to send.
    </param>
    <exception cref="T:System.ArgumentNullException">
    <para><paramref name="message"/> is <see langword="null"/>.</para>
    </exception>
</member>
<member name="M:NBS.Core.Net.Mail.MailMessageExtensions.&lt;G&gt;$BD2D78579B3497A706F11AA8C4CDB9C3.Send(NBS.Core.Net.Mail.ISmtpClientFactory)">
    <summary>
    Sends the message using the default SMTP settings.
    </summary>
    <param name="smtpClientFactory">
    The <see cref="T:NBS.Core.Net.Mail.ISmtpClientFactory"/>.
    </param>
    <exception cref="T:System.ArgumentNullException">
    <para><paramref name="smtpClientFactory"/> is <see langword="null"/>.</para>
    </exception>
</member>
```

Tools like [SHFB](https://github.com/EWSoftware/SHFB/issues/1155) are thus unable to generate the correct documentation for the method, reporting missing documentation for the `message` parameter, and not including the *"message is null"* `ArgumentNullException`.

